     <div type="dedication">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>
      <hi>Ad mare riuuli.</hi> TO MY LOVING FRIEND MASTER MICHAEL DRAYTON.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>THe tender labour of my wearie pen,</l>
      <l>And doubtfull triall of my first-borne rimes,</l>
      <l>Loaths to adorne the triumphs of those men,</l>
      <l>Which hold the raines of fortune, and the times:</l>
      <l>Only to thee, which art with ioy possest</l>
      <l>Of the faire hill, where troupes of Poets band,</l>
      <l>Where thou enthron'd with Laurell garlands blest,</l>
      <l>Maist lift me vp with thy propitious hand;</l>
      <l>I send this poëme, which for nought doth care,</l>
      <l>But words for words, and loue for loue to share.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>—nam{que} tu solebas</hi>
      </l>
      <l>
         <hi>Meas esse aliquid putare nugas.</hi>
      </l>
   </lg>
</div>
